[19:50] <Util> For example, there were several efforts to trim fat from Parrot in the last few months. If those branches could be spoken-to by their authors (inactive or otherwise), those of us currently active might move them forward, or test them, or benchmark them against "full-fat" Parrot, or even "land" the branches.
[19:52] <Util> We have gradually slid from goals and milestones into everyone "doing your own thing".
[19:52] <Util> DYOT *can* be viable, it only works long-term when everyone is public and vocal about their plans and activities, so that feedback moves some people away from less fruitful efforts, and onto helping with more fruitful (or more tuit-needy) endeavors.
